                    const addMaximumScaleToMetaViewport = () => \{\
                  const el = document.querySelector('meta[name=viewport]');\
                \
                  if (el !== null) \{\
                    let content = el.getAttribute('content');\
                    let re = /maximum\\-scale=[0-9\\.]+/g;\
                \
                    if (re.test(content)) \{\
                        content = content.replace(re, 'maximum-scale=1.0');\
                    \} else \{\
                        content = [content, 'maximum-scale=1.0'].join(', ')\
                    \}\
                \
                    el.setAttribute('content', content);\

<input type="number" class="ea-tax-input full-width disable-number-picker" data-price-locales="en-US" value="0" min="0" max="2147483647" step="1" placeholder="Enter Amount..." _="set :priceLocales to my [@data-price-locales]\
\
def constrainValue(rawValue)\
  set value to Math.round(Number(rawValue))\
  if isNaN(value)\
    set value to 0\
  end\
  return Math.max(my min, Math.min(my max, value))\
end\
\
on change\
  set my value to constrainValue(my valueAsNumber)\
end\
      \
on input (get the valueAsNumber of me)\
  set priceInput to constrainValue(it)\
  set tax to frontend.futbin.frontenddata.calculateEaTax(priceInput)\
  set net to frontend.futbin.frontenddata.calculateNetPrice(priceInput)\
  \
  put Number(tax).toLocaleString(:priceLocales) into .ea-tax\
  put Number(net).toLocaleString(:priceLocales) into .after-tax\
end"></div>\
                  <hr>\
                  <div class="xs-column">\
                    <div class="row space-between">\
                      <div>Tax (5%):</div>\
                      <div class="ea-tax bold">0</div>\
                    </div>\
                    <div class="row space-between">\
                      <div>Earnings after tax:</div>\
                      <div class="after-tax bold">0</div>\
                    </div>\
                    <hr>\
<button class="og-button og-button-normal  og-button-primary centered" _="on click \
                                    put '0' into .ea-tax.innerHTML\
                                    put '0' into .after-tax.innerHTML\
                                    put '0' into .sell-for.innerHTML \
                                    set the (value of .ea-tax-input) to '0'\
                                    end">Reset Calculator</button></div>\
                </div>\

\
def constrainValue(rawValue)\
  set value to Math.round(Number(rawValue))\
  if isNaN(value)\
    set value to 0\
  end\
  return Math.max(my min, Math.min(my max, value))\
end\
\
on change\
  set my value to constrainValue(my valueAsNumber)\
end\
      \
on input (get the valueAsNumber of me)\
  set priceInput to constrainValue(it)\
  set tax to frontend.futbin.frontenddata.calculateEaTax(priceInput)\
  set net to frontend.futbin.frontenddata.calculateNetPrice(priceInput)\
  \
  put Number(tax).toLocaleString(:priceLocales) into .ea-tax\
  put Number(net).toLocaleString(:priceLocales) into .after-tax\
end"></div>\

                  </div>\

                                    put '0' into .after-tax.innerHTML\

                                    end">Reset Calculator</button></div>\

                      <div class="filter-elements-search-wrapper">\
                        <div class="full-width-filter-item first-filter-item-border filter-search-wrapper"><input class="search-filter" _="on keyup\
                        set input to my value.toLowerCase()\
                        set results to []\
                        set searchWrapper to closest parent .filter-elements-search-wrapper\
                        set resultsSeparator to .results-separator in searchWrapper\
                        set resultsDiv to .filter-search-results in searchWrapper\
                        set innerHTML of resultsDiv to ''\
                        if input.length > 1\
                            set eles to <li/> in .searchable-leagues\
                            for ele in eles \
                                if @data-filter-search-key of ele contains input\
                                    append ele to results\
                                end\
                            end\
                        end\
                        if results is empty\
                            add .hidden to resultsSeparator\
                        else\
                            remove .hidden from resultsSeparator\
                            for result in results\
                                put outerHTML of result at end of resultsDiv\
                            end \
                        end" placeholder="Search"></div>\

on click add .gtSmartphone-only to .selected-filters-wrapper\
on click\
    set iWasActive to I match .active\
    if not iWasActive\
        wait 0s\
        toggle .active on next .dropdown-content \
        toggle .active on me\
    end\
end \
on click from window\
    remove .active from next .dropdown-content\
    remove .active from me\
end">\

                      <div class="filter-elements-search-wrapper">\
                        <div class="full-width-filter-item first-filter-item-border filter-search-wrapper"><input class="search-filter" _="on keyup\
                        set input to my value.toLowerCase()\
                        set results to []\
                        set searchWrapper to closest parent .filter-elements-search-wrapper\
                        set resultsSeparator to .results-separator in searchWrapper\
                        set resultsDiv to .filter-search-results in searchWrapper\
                        set innerHTML of resultsDiv to ''\
                        if input.length > 1\
                            set eles to <li/> in .searchable-nations\
                            for ele in eles \
                                if @data-filter-search-key of ele contains input\
                                    append ele to results\
                                end\
                            end\
                        end\
                        if results is empty\
                            add .hidden to resultsSeparator\
                        else\
                            remove .hidden from resultsSeparator\
                            for result in results\
                                put outerHTML of result at end of resultsDiv\
                            end \
                        end" placeholder="Search"></div>\

                <div class="dropdown-element dropdown-click"><button class="dropdown-title xs-row" _="on click remove .gtSmartphone-only from next .players-filters-wrapper-smartphone\
on click add .gtSmartphone-only to .selected-filters-wrapper\
on click\
    set iWasActive to I match .active\
    if not iWasActive\
        wait 0s\
        toggle .active on next .dropdown-content \
        toggle .active on me\
    end\
end \
on click from window\
    remove .active from next .dropdown-content\
    remove .active from me\
end">\

                                 remove .gtSmartphone-only from .selected-filters-wrapper\
                                 remove .scroll-lock from body\
                              end"><i class="far fa-xmark"></i></button></div>\
                    <ul class="dropdown-list">\
                      <div class="filter-elements-search-wrapper">\
                        <div class="full-width-filter-item first-filter-item-border filter-search-wrapper"><input class="search-filter" _="on keyup\
                        set input to my value.toLowerCase()\
                        set results to []\
                        set searchWrapper to closest parent .filter-elements-search-wrapper\
                        set resultsSeparator to .results-separator in searchWrapper\
                        set resultsDiv to .filter-search-results in searchWrapper\
                        set innerHTML of resultsDiv to ''\
                        if input.length > 1\
                            set eles to <li/> in .searchable-clubs\
                            for ele in eles \
                                if @data-filter-search-key of ele contains input\
                                    append ele to results\
                                end\
                            end\
                        end\
                        if results is empty\
                            add .hidden to resultsSeparator\
                        else\
                            remove .hidden from resultsSeparator\
                            for result in results\
                                put outerHTML of result at end of resultsDiv\
                            end \
                        end" placeholder="Search"></div>\
                        <ul class="filter-search-results"></ul>\
                        <hr class="results-separator hidden">\
                      </div>\

                        set input to my value.toLowerCase()\
                        set eles to <li/> in .searchable-playstyles                          \
                        for ele in eles                                                         \
                            set normalizedName to @data-filter-search-key of ele                             \
                            if not (normalizedName contains input) and input.length > 1\
                                add .hidden to ele\
                            otherwise\
                                remove .hidden from ele                                \
                            end                            \
                        end\
                        set eles to <label/> in .searchable-playstyles \
                        set lastLabel to null\
                        set visibleChild to 0\
                        for ele in eles                              \
                            if ele matches .search-group-label then                                  \
                                if lastLabel is not null then\
                                    if visibleChild is 1 then\
                                        show lastLabel\
                                    else\
                                        hide lastLabel\
                                    end\
                                end\
                                set visibleChild to 0\
                                set lastLabel to ele\
                            else\
                                set listItem to ele.parentElement                                \
                                if not (listItem matches .hidden) then                                                                     \
                                   set visibleChild to 1  \
                                end\
                            end\

                    <div _="def validateRating(min, max)\
                     if (not Number.isInteger(min) or min is less than 40 or min is greater than 99) \
                         return &quot;Min Rating must be a number between 40 and 99&quot;\
                     end\
                     if (not Number.isInteger(max) or max is less than 40 or max is greater than 99) \
                         return &quot;Max Rating must be a number between 40 and 99&quot;\
                     end\
                     if (min is greater than max) \
                         return &quot;Min Rating must be less than Max Rating&quot;\
                     end\
                 end">\
                      <ul class="dropdown-list margin-inherit xs-column top-margin-smartphone-s"><input class="search-filter rating-filter-min-rating-input" placeholder="Min Rating"><input class="search-filter rating-filter-max-rating-input" placeholder="Max Rating">\
                        <div class="select-add-filters-button bottom-button font-extra-extra-small centered small-row" _="on click\
                             set minInput to getFormValues(&quot;rating-filter-min-rating-input&quot;)\
                             set maxInput to getFormValues(&quot;rating-filter-max-rating-input&quot;)\
                             if (minInput is empty) set minInt to 40 otherwise set minInt to parseInt(minInput) end\
                             if (maxInput is empty) set maxInt to 99 otherwise set maxInt to parseInt(maxInput) end\
                             then set validationError to validateRating(minInt, maxInt) \
                             if validationError is not null call showFeedbackPopup(&quot;Invalid rating range&quot;, validationError) then exit end\
                             set window.location.search to setUrlParams(&quot;player_rating&quot;, minInt + &quot;-&quot; + maxInt, &quot;page&quot;, null)\
                         end"><i class="fa fa-search"></i>Apply</div>\
                      </ul>\
                    </div>\

                        <li class="dropdown-list-item"><label class=" small-row"><input type="radio" name="foot-filter-radio" value="Right"><img src="/design2/img/static/filters/foot-right.svg" width="14" height="14" loading="lazy">Right</label></li>\
                        <div class="select-add-filters-button bottom-button font-extra-extra-small centered small-row" _="on click\
                                 set selectedFoot to getCheckedFormValues(&quot;foot-filter-radio&quot;)\
                                 set newParams to setUrlParams(&quot;foot&quot;, selectedFoot, &quot;page&quot;, null)\
                                 set window.location.search to newParams\

                <script>function feetAndInchesToCentimeters(feet, inches) \{\
    let parsedFeet = parseInt(feet)\
    let parsedInches = parseInt(inches)\
    if (isNaN(parsedFeet) || isNaN(parsedInches)) \{\
        return null\
    \}\
    let totalInches = parsedFeet * 12 + parsedInches;\
    return totalInches * 2.54;\
\}\
\
function lbsToKilo(lbs) \{\
    let parsedLbs = parseInt(lbs)\
    if (isNaN(parsedLbs)) \{\
        return null\
    \}\
    return parsedLbs * 0.453592;\
\}\
\
function checkForValidIntegerInput(input) \{\
    if (isNaN(parseInt(input))) \{\
        return null\
    \} else \{\
        return input\
    \}\
\}</script>\

                          </div>\
                          <div class="select-add-filters-button bottom-button font-extra-extra-small centered small-row" _="on click\
    set minHeightInFeet to getFormValues(&quot;min-height-feet&quot;)\
    set maxHeightInFeet to getFormValues(&quot;max-height-feet&quot;)\
    set minHeightInInches to getFormValues(&quot;min-height-inches&quot;)\
    set maxHeightInInches to getFormValues(&quot;max-height-inches&quot;)\
    set minHeight to getFormValues(&quot;min-height-centimeter&quot;)\
    set maxHeight to getFormValues(&quot;max-height-centimeter&quot;)\
    set errorTitle to &quot;Invalid Input&quot;\
    set errorDescription to &quot;Your input is not valid&quot;\
    if (first .height-cm-input matches .hidden)\
        set noInputs to (minHeightInFeet is empty and maxHeightInFeet is empty)\
        set noValidMinHeightInFeet to (minHeightInFeet is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(minHeightInFeet) is null)\
        set noValidMaxHeightInFeet to (maxHeightInFeet is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(maxHeightInFeet) is null)\
        set noValidMinHeightInInches to (minHeightInFeet is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(minHeightInFeet) is null)\
        set noValidMaxHeightInInches to (maxHeightInFeet is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(maxHeightInFeet) is null)\
        if noInputs or noValidMinHeightInFeet or noValidMaxHeightInFeet or noValidMinHeightInInches or noValidMaxHeightInInches call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\
\
        if (minHeightInFeet is empty) set minHeight to 152 \
        else \
            if (minHeightInInches is empty) set minHeight to Math.floor(feetAndInchesToCentimeters(minHeightInFeet, 0))\
            else set minHeight to Math.floor(feetAndInchesToCentimeters(minHeightInFeet, minHeightInInches)) end\
        end\
        if (maxHeightInFeet is empty) set maxHeight to 220 \
        else \
            if (maxHeightInInches is empty) set maxHeight to Math.ceil(feetAndInchesToCentimeters(maxHeightInFeet, 11))\
            else set maxHeight to Math.ceil(feetAndInchesToCentimeters(maxHeightInFeet, maxHeightInInches))\
            end\
        end\
    else \
        set noInputs to (minHeight is empty and maxHeight is empty)\
        set noValidMinHeight to (minHeight is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(minHeight) is null)\
        set noValidMaxHeight to (maxHeight is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(maxHeight) is null)\
        if noInputs or noValidMinHeight or noValidMaxHeight call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\
        if (minHeight is empty) set minHeight to 152 end\
        if (maxHeight is empty) set maxHeight to 220 end\
    end\
    \
    if (minHeight is null) call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\
    if (maxHeight is null) call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\
    set window.location.search to setUrlParams(&quot;player_height&quot;, minHeight + &quot;-&quot; + maxHeight)\
end"><i class="fa fa-search"></i>Apply Height</div>\

    if first .weight-kg-input matches .hidden\

        if noInputsLbs or noValidMinWeightLbs or noValidMaxWeightLbs call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\

        set noValidMaxWeight to (maxWeight is not empty and checkForValidIntegerInput(maxWeight) is null)\
        if noInputs or noValidMinWeight or noValidMaxWeight call showFeedbackPopup(errorTitle, errorDescription) exit end\
        if (minWeight is empty) set minWeight to 0 end\
        if (maxWeight is empty) set maxWeight to 200 end\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover-1962126813&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover-1962126813&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover-1962126813 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover-1962126813\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover-1962126813.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover-1962126813.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover-1962126813\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover-1962126813\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover-1962126813\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover-1962126813\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\
        add .top-left to #hover-1962126813\
   else if isBelowViewport                                    -- element bottom\
        add .bottom-left to #hover-1962126813\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--11287429&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover--11287429&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--11287429 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--11287429\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover--11287429.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover--11287429.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover--11287429\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover--11287429\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover--11287429\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover--11287429\
         end\

   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--2044800700&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover--2044800700&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\

    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--2044800700 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--2044800700\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \

    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\

    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\

    set #hover--2044800700.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\

    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover--2044800700\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\

            add .top-right to #hover--2044800700\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover--2044800700\
         else                                               -- element mid right\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover-1213849466&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover-1213849466&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover-1213849466 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover-1213849466\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover-1213849466.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover-1213849466.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover-1213849466\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover-1213849466\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover-1213849466\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover-1213849466\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\
        add .top-left to #hover-1213849466\
   else if isBelowViewport                                    -- element bottom\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--1426815640&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover--1426815640&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\

\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--1426815640 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--1426815640\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover--1426815640.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover--1426815640.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover--1426815640\

    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\

            add .top-right to #hover--1426815640\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover--1426815640\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover--1426815640\

on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--219471062&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover--219471062&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--219471062 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--219471062\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \

        exit\

    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\

    set #hover--219471062.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\

    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\

            add .bottom-right to #hover--219471062\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover--219471062\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover-836535060&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover-836535060&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover-836535060 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover-836535060\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover-836535060.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover-836535060.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover-836535060\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover-836535060\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover-836535060\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover-836535060\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\
        add .top-left to #hover-836535060\
   else if isBelowViewport                                    -- element bottom\
        add .bottom-left to #hover-836535060\

\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover-1159980683&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover-1159980683&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover-1159980683 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover-1159980683\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\

    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover-1159980683.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover-1159980683.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover-1159980683\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover-1159980683\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover-1159980683\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover-1159980683\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\

                      </a>\
                      <div class="table-player-info">\
                        <div class="player-hover-container-wrapper" title="" data-player-hover-location="/25/playerhover/12" _="set :fetched to false\
\
on mouseenter\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--52887450&quot;) === null)\
        put `<div id=&quot;hover--52887450&quot; class=&quot;player-hover-container&quot; hidden />` at the end of <body/>\
    end\
\
    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--52887450 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--52887450\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\
    \
on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover--52887450.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover--52887450.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover--52887450\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover--52887450\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover--52887450\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover--52887450\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\
        add .top-left to #hover--52887450\
   else if isBelowViewport                                    -- element bottom\
        add .bottom-left to #hover--52887450\
   end"><a href="/25/player/12/tim-howard" class="table-player-name">Tim Howard</a></div>\

        exit\

\
    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover-1165003139&quot;) === null)\

    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\

        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover-1165003139 until mouseleave\
        end\

            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover-1165003139\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\

on mousemove (clientX, clientY) measure my top, right, bottom then\
    if window.matchMedia( &quot;(hover: none)&quot; ).matches\
        exit\
    end\
\
    set cursorPositionXTotal to clientX + window.pageXOffset\
    set cursorPositionYTotal to clientY + window.pageYOffset\
    set #hover--1117065847.style.left to cursorPositionXTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    set #hover--1117065847.style.top to cursorPositionYTotal + &quot;px&quot;\
    \
    set containerHeight to 600\
    set containerWidth to 350\
    set isAboveViewport to (top * 2) < containerHeight\
    set isBelowViewport to (window.innerHeight - bottom) < (containerHeight / 2)\
    \
    remove .bottom-left .top-left .mid-right .bottom-right .top-right from #hover--1117065847\
    \
    if (window.innerWidth - right) < containerWidth         -- SHOW HOVER ON LEFT SIDE\
         if isAboveViewport                                      -- element upper right\
            add .top-right to #hover--1117065847\
         else if isBelowViewport                              -- element lower right\
            add .bottom-right to #hover--1117065847\
         else                                               -- element mid right\
            add .mid-right to #hover--1117065847\
         end\
                                                            -- SHOW HOVER ON RIGHT SIDE\
   else if isAboveViewport                                       -- element top\
        add .top-left to #hover--1117065847\
   else if isBelowViewport                                    -- element bottom\
        add .bottom-left to #hover--1117065847\

        exit\
    end\

    if (document.getElementById(&quot;hover--647976110&quot;) === null)\

    wait for mouseleave or 350ms\
    if the result's type is not 'mouseleave'\
        async do \
             toggle [@hidden] on #hover--647976110 until mouseleave\
        end\
        if :fetched is false\
            set response to fetch(`$\{@data-player-hover-location\}`)\
            if response.ok\
                put the response.text() into #hover--647976110\
            end\
            set :fetched to true\
        end\
    end\

    <script>\
                        function getFormValues(inputName)\{\
                            return toArraySingleElementOrNull(document.querySelectorAll('.'+inputName))\
                        \}\
                    \
                        function getCheckedFormValues(inputName)\{\
                            return toArraySingleElementOrNull(document.querySelectorAll('input[name='+inputName+']:checked'))\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function getClassAttributes(className, attributeName)\{\
                            var attrValues = [];\
                            document.querySelectorAll('.'+className+'['+attributeName+']').forEach(function(div) \{\
                                attrValues.push(div.getAttribute(attributeName));\
                            \});\
                            if(attrValues.length === 0) return null\
                            else return attrValues\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function getTrueIfChecked(inputName)\{\
                            if (document.querySelectorAll('input[name='+inputName+']:checked').length > 0)\{ \
                                return true\
                            \} else \{\
                                return null\
                            \}\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function toArraySingleElementOrNull(input)\{\
                            let selected = Array.from(input).map((button) => button.value)\
                            if (selected.length > 1)\{\
                                return selected;\
                            \} else if (selected.length == 1)\{\
                                return selected[0];\
                            \} else \{\
                                return null;\
                            \}\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function strcmp(a, b) \{\
                            if (a.toString() < b.toString()) return -1;\
                            if (a.toString() > b.toString()) return 1;\
                            return 0;\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function getCurrentParams() \{\
                            return getSearchParamsObject(window.location.search)\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function getSearchParamsObject(search) \{\
                            let params = \{\}\
                            new URLSearchParams(search).forEach((value, key) => \{\
                                if (key in params) \{\
                                    if (Array.isArray(params[key])) \{\
                                        params[key].push(value)\
                                    \} else \{\
                                        params[key] = [params[key], value]\
                                    \}\
                                \} else \{\
                                    params[key] = value\
                                \}\
                            \});\
                            return params;\
                        \}\
                        \
                        function computeNextParams(currentParams, arguments) \{\
                            let nextParams = currentParams\
                            for (let i = 0; i + 1 < arguments.length; i += 2) \{\
                                const key = arguments[i];\
                                const value = arguments[i + 1];\
                                if (value != null) \{\
                                    if (Array.isArray(value)) \{\
                                        if (value.length > 1)\{\
                                            nextParams[key] = value.join(",");\
                                        \} else \{\
                                            nextParams[key] = value;\
                                        \}\
                                    \} else \{\
                                        nextParams[key] = value;\
                                    \}\
                                \} else \{\
                                    delete nextParams[key];\
                                \}\
                            \}\
                            return nextParams\
                        \}\
                                \
                        \
                        function paramArrayToString(params) \{\
                            // convert object to array\
                            const result = Object.entries(params);\
    \
                            // Sort values for better cache hit rate\
                            result.forEach((e) => \{ if (Array.isArray(e[1]))\{ e[1].sort() \} \});\
    \
                            // Sort params for better cache hit rate\
                            result.sort((a, b) => strcmp(a[0], b[0]));\
                                \
                            if (result.length == 0)\{\
                                return ""\
                            \} else \{\
                                const prms = new URLSearchParams();\
                                result.forEach((e) => \{\
                                    if (Array.isArray(e[1]))\{\
                                        e[1].forEach((v) => prms.append(e[0], v));\
                                    \} else \{\
                                        prms.append(e[0], e[1]);\
                                    \}\
                                \});\
                                const res = "?" + prms.toString();\
                                return res;\
                            \}\
                        \}\
                       \
                        /*\
                        Overwrites params in the query. Array values are joined with , and empty values are removed.\
                        Works for any number of name value pairs.\
                        */\
                        function setUrlParams(name, value, name2, value2)\{\
                            return updateUrlParams(window.location.search, ...arguments)\
                        \}\
                        \
                        /*\
                        Overwrites params in the given query search. Array values are joined with , and empty values are removed.\
                        Works for any number of name value pairs.\
                        */\
                        function updateUrlParams(currentSearch, name, value, name2, value2)\{\
                            let currentParams = getSearchParamsObject(currentSearch)\
                            let params = computeNextParams(currentParams, Array.from(arguments).slice(1))\
                            return paramArrayToString(params)\
                        \}\
                       \
                        /* \
                        Overwrites params in the query, keeping none of the current params.\
                        Array values are joined with , and empty values are removed.\
                        Works for any number of name value pairs.\
                        */ \
                        function overwriteUrlParams(name, value, name2, value2) \{\
                            let params = computeNextParams([], arguments);\
                            return paramArrayToString(params)\
                        \}\
                        </script>\
